devdoc.author: MediVault Team
devdoc.details: Enables patients to store encrypted health metrics and control access Key Features: - Health metrics are encrypted client-side before submission - Only encrypted values are stored on-chain - Per-metric permission control (Blood Pressure, Heart Rate, Glucose) - Patients grant/revoke access to doctors, hospitals, insurers Permission Bitmask: - Bit 0 (1): Blood Pressure - Bit 1 (2): Heart Rate - Bit 2 (4): Glucose Level - All metrics (7): Full access

returns._0: Unix timestamp of last update (0 if no record)

getRecord(address).details: Returns zero handles if patient hasn't submitted records

returns._0: Tuple of (bloodPressure, heartRate, glucoseLevel) encrypted handles

grantAccess(address,uint8).details: Permissions are cumulative - calling with new mask updates the stored value

params.viewer: Address to grant permissions to (doctor, hospital, etc.)

returns._0: True if the patient has initialized their health record

revokeAccess(address,uint8).details: FHE ACL cannot be revoked on existing ciphertexts, but new records      will not include the revoked viewer in the allow list

params.metricMask: Bitmask of metrics to revoke (use 7 to clear all)

submitRecord(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32,byt.details: Encrypts metrics client-side before calling this function

params.inputProof: Zama relayer input proof for verification
